any?\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cYour mother.\u201d The man asked, \u201cThen who?\u201d The Prophet said \u201cYour mother.\u201d The man asked again, \u201cThen who?\u201d The Prophet said, \"Your mother.\"\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":6719,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/09\/20\/abu-bakr-khalifah-imam-salat\/","url_meta":{"origin":15335,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Khilafah: The Prophet orders Abu Bakr to lead prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 20, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Musa reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, became ill, and when his condition was critical, he said, \u201cTell Abu Bakr to lead the people in prayer.\u201d Aisha said, \u201cHe is a soft-hearted man. He will not be able to lead in your place.\u201d The Prophet said\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":32985,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/07\/30\/sins-fall-away-wudu-salat\/","url_meta":{"origin":15335,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Wudu: Sins fall away by ablution and prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 30, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"\u2018Amr ibn \u2018Abasah reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cNone of you approach ablution and rinse his mouth and nose but that the sins of his face, mouth, and nose fall away. He does not wash his face as Allah commanded him